station-event-deathsquad-enroute = All contracts with crew have been terminated. Security is to lay down arms, and former crew are required to surrender to Nanotrasen. Failure to do so will result in capital punishment. Command is to peacefully surrender first, to set an example for the former crew.
station-event-emergencyresponseteam-generic-enroute = Emergency Response Team enroute. Glory to Nanotrasen.
station-event-cburn-enroute = A Sever biohazard has been detected on station, and Central Command has dispatched a CBURN Response team. All non-Medical or Security staff are to shelter in place immediately, and infected crew are to be restrained or terminated. CBURN now holds authority over all station affairs, please wait for further instructions and cooperate with CBURN teams.
station-event-emergencyresponseteam-engineering-enroute = Central Command has dispatched a Engineering Response Team to the station. Please cooperate with ERT Members and do everything in your power to accomodate their needs. Non-Engineering crew are to stay away from damaged areas or uncontrolled engines. Please locate personal Internals and wait for further instruction.
station-event-emergencyresponseteam-security-enroute = Central Command has dispatched a Security Response Team to the station. Please cooperate with ERT Members and do everything in your power to accomodate their needs. ERT Members hold authority over the Captain. Crew members are advised to shelter in place and wait for instructions from Station Command or Central Command.
station-event-emergencyresponseteam-medical-enroute = Central Command has dispatched a Medical Response Team to the station. Please cooperate with ERT Members and do everything in your power to accomodate their needs. Remaining Medical staff are advised to cooperate with ERT members in stabilization efforts. ERT Members hold authority over the Chief Medical Officer. 
station-event-emergencyresponseteam-chaplain-enroute = Large quantities of unauthorized magical activities have been detected aboard the station. A special emergency response team has been deployed.
